.TH "svc_register" 9 "svc_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
svc_register \- register an RPC service with the local portmapper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" svc_register
.BI "(const struct svc_serv *serv "  ","
.BI "struct net *net "  ","
.BI "const int family "  ","
.BI "const unsigned short proto "  ","
.BI "const unsigned short port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "serv" 12
svc_serv struct for the service to register
.IP "net" 12
net namespace for the service to register
.IP "family" 12
protocol family of service's listener socket
.IP "proto" 12
transport protocol number to advertise
.IP "port" 12
port to advertise
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Service is registered for any address in the passed-in protocol family
